    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Matthew",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 16,
        "summary": "Jesus warns against the doctrine of the Pharisees and Sadducees\u2014Peter testifies that Jesus is the Christ and is promised the keys of the kingdom\u2014Jesus foretells His death and resurrection.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "The Pharisees also with the Sadducees came, and tempting desired him that he would shew them a sign from heaven.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Heaven.",
                        "start": 105,
                        "end": 111
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He answered and said unto them, When it is evening, ye say, It will be fair weather: for the sky is red.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 26:5.",
                        "start": 3,
                        "end": 11
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And in the morning, It will be foul weather to day: for the sky is red and lowring. O ye hypocrites, ye can discern the face of the sky; but can ye not discern the signs of the times?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0dark, gloomy.",
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 82
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hypocrisy.",
                        "start": 89,
                        "end": 99
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Pet. 3:4 (3\u201310).",
                        "start": 164,
                        "end": 169
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Esth. 1:13.",
                        "start": 177,
                        "end": 182
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 88
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 152,
                        "end": 159
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A wicked and adulterous generation seeketh after a sign; and there shall no sign be given unto it, but the sign of the prophet Jonas. And he left them, and departed.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Adulterer.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mark 8:12 (11\u201321).",
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jonah 1:17.",
                        "start": 107,
                        "end": 111
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Death of.",
                        "start": 127,
                        "end": 132
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And when his disciples were come to the other side, they had forgotten to take bread.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Then Jesus said unto them, Take heed and beware of the leaven of the Pharisees and of the Sadducees.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Leaven.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 61
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And they reasoned among themselves, saying, It is because we have taken no bread.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 49
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Which when Jesus perceived, he said unto them, O ye of little faith, why reason ye among yourselves, because ye have brought no bread?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Do ye not yet understand, neither remember the five loaves of the five thousand, and how many baskets ye took up?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Neither the seven loaves of the four thousand, and how many baskets ye took up?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "How is it that ye do not understand that I spake it not to you concerning bread, that ye should beware of the leaven of the Pharisees and of the Sadducees?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 51
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Then understood they how that he bade them not beware of the leaven of bread, but of the doctrine of the Pharisees and of the Sadducees.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 15:9.",
                        "start": 89,
                        "end": 97
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 22:23 (23\u201333).",
                        "start": 126,
                        "end": 135
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 42
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "When Jesus came into the coasts of C\u00e6sarea Philippi, he asked his disciples, saying, Whom do men say that I the Son of man am?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p13",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And they said, Some say that thou art John the Baptist: some, Elias; and others, Jeremias, or one of the prophets.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0Elijah.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 67
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 37
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He saith unto them, But whom say ye that I am?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0The plural pronoun used here in the Greek indicates that Jesus asked this question of all the apostles and not just one of them.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 35
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Simon Peter answered and said, Thou art the Christ, the Son of the living God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Loyalty.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 54
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Divine Sonship.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 63
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Body of, Corporeal Nature.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 81
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Jesus answered and said unto him, Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona: for flesh and blood hath not revealed it unto thee, but my Father which is in heaven.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0Son of Jonah.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 70
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Revelation; Testimony; Witness.",
                        "start": 101,
                        "end": 109
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 110,
                        "end": 112
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And I say also unto thee, That thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church; and the gates of hell shall not prevail against it.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Here is a subtle wordplay upon \u201cPeter\u201d (Greek petros = small rock) and \u201crock\u201d (Greek petra = bedrock). Christ is the Stone of Israel. John 1:42; 1\u00a0Cor. 3:11 (9\u201311); 10:4; D&C 50:44; 128:10. TG\u00a0Rock.",
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 65
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Church Organization; Jesus Christ, Head of the Church.",
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 88
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hell.",
                        "start": 107,
                        "end": 111
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 17:8; 21:6.",
                        "start": 122,
                        "end": 129
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 1216
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And I will give unto thee the keys of the kingdom of heaven: and whatsoever thou shalt bind on earth shall be bound in heaven: and whatsoever thou shalt loose on earth shall be loosed in heaven.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 7:7; 27:13. TG\u00a0Delegation of Responsibility; God, Gifts of.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Apostles; Priesthood; Priesthood, Authority; Priesthood, History of; Priesthood, Keys of.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 34
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Kingdom of God, on Earth.",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 49
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hel. 10:7 (5\u201311); D&C 138:58 (58\u201360). TG\u00a0Genealogy and Temple Work; Marriage, Celestial; Salvation for the Dead; Sealing.",
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 91
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Then charged he his disciples that they should tell no man that he was Jesus the Christ.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Messiah.",
                        "start": 81,
                        "end": 87
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "From that time forth began Jesus to shew unto his disciples, how that he must go unto Jerusalem, and suffer many things of the elders and chief priests and scribes, and be killed, and be raised again the third day.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Resurrection.",
                        "start": 187,
                        "end": 193
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p21",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Then Peter took him, and began to rebuke him, saying, Be it far from thee, Lord: this shall not be unto thee.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But he turned, and said unto Peter, Get thee behind me, Satan: thou art an offence unto me: for thou savourest not the things that be of God, but those that be of men.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hel. 10:4 (4\u20135).",
                        "start": 101,
                        "end": 110
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Then said Jesus unto his disciples, If any man will come after me, let him deny himself, and take up his cross, and follow me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Matt. 16:25\u201329 (Appendix).",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 4
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Self-Mastery.",
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 79
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 10:38; 3\u00a0Ne. 12:30.",
                        "start": 105,
                        "end": 110
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Philip. 3:17 (13\u201321); 2\u00a0Ne. 31:12 (12\u201313).",
                        "start": 116,
                        "end": 122
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Matt. 16:25\u201326 \u2026 me. And now for a man to take up his cross, is to deny himself all ungodliness, and every worldly lust, and keep my commandments.",
                        "start": 123,
                        "end": 125
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 46
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For whosoever will save his life shall lose it: and whosoever will lose his life for my sake shall find it.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Self-Mastery; Self-Sacrifice.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 71
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Abundant Life.",
                        "start": 99,
                        "end": 103
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For what is a man profited, if he shall gain the whole world, and lose his own soul? or what shall a man give in exchange for his soul?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Sam. 12:21; Prov. 13:7; Eccl. 1:3 (2\u20133).",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 26
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Job 27:8. TG\u00a0Selfishness; Treasure.",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 44
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Worldliness.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 60
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 9:25.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 70
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Mortality; Soul.",
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 83
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For the Son of man shall come in the glory of his Father with his angels; and then he shall reward every man according to his works.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Son of Man.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Glory; Jesus Christ, Glory of; Jesus Christ, Second Coming.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Judge; Judgment, the Last; Retribution; Reward.",
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 98
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 24:12. TG\u00a0Good Works.",
                        "start": 126,
                        "end": 131
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p27",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Verily I say unto you, There be some standing here, which shall not taste of death, till they see the Son of man coming in his kingdom.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Translated Beings.",
                        "start": 77,
                        "end": 82
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Millennium.",
                        "start": 127,
                        "end": 134
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}